\v 5  Ahab told \w Obadiah|strong="H5662"\w*, “\w Go|strong="H3212"\w* \w through|strong="H3212"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* land \w to|strong="H3212"\w* \w all|strong="H3605"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w springs|strong="H4599"\w* \w and|strong="H3212"\w* \w valleys|strong="H5158"\w*. Maybe \w we|strong="H3068"\w* \w can|strong="H3808"\w* \w find|strong="H4672"\w* \w some|strong="H3605"\w* grazing areas \w so|strong="H3808"\w* \w we|strong="H3068"\w* \w can|strong="H3808"\w* \w keep|strong="H2421"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w horses|strong="H5483"\w* \w and|strong="H3212"\w* \w mules|strong="H6505"\w* \w alive|strong="H2421"\w* \w and|strong="H3212"\w* \w not|strong="H3808"\w* \w have|strong="H4672"\w* \w to|strong="H3212"\w* \w kill|strong="H3772"\w* \w some|strong="H3605"\w* \w of|strong="H4325"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w animals|strong="H2421"\w*.”  
